.TH TASH 1 "April 2026" "v@PROJECT_VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tash \- Tavakkoli's Shell, a modern Unix shell with syntax highlighting, autosuggestions, themes, and optional AI assistance
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tash
.RI [ script ]
.br
.B tash
.B --version
.br
.B tash
.B --features
.br
.B tash
.B --benchmark
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tash
is a modern Unix shell written in C++. It supports standard shell features — pipes, redirection, subshells, heredocs, command substitution, glob expansion, job control, aliases, history, and POSIX-style \fBtrap\fR handlers — alongside a plugin architecture that powers smart completions (Fish + Fig + man-page), configurable themes, rich terminal output, a SQLite-backed history, and an optional AI assistant.
.PP
If a
.I script
file is given as an argument, tash executes it and exits. Otherwise, it starts an interactive session.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --version, --features, -V
Print the version and the list of compiled-in features (e.g. \fB+ai +sqlite-history\fR) and exit. Tokens prefixed with \fB-\fR indicate a feature was compiled out because its dependency was missing at build time.
.TP
.B --benchmark
Print a staged startup-time breakdown and exit.
.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
.SS Navigation
.TP
.B cd \fR[\fIdir\fR]
Change directory. No argument goes to \fB$HOME\fR. \fBcd -\fR returns to the previous directory. Auto-cd: typing a bare directory name \fBcd\fRs into it.
.TP
.B pwd
Print the current working directory.
.TP
.B z \fIpattern\fR
Jump to the most-visited directory matching \fIpattern\fR (frecency-ranked).
.TP
.B pushd \fIdir\fR, popd, dirs
Directory-stack manipulation.
.SS Environment & aliases
.TP
.B export \fR[\fIVAR=value\fR]
Set an environment variable. No argument lists all.
.TP
.B unset \fIVAR\fR
Remove an environment variable.
.TP
.B alias \fR[\fIname=value\fR]
Define an alias. No argument lists all. Tash reminds you when you type a command for which you have an alias.
.TP
.B unalias \fIname\fR
Remove an alias.
.SS History
.TP
.B history \fR[\fI--here|--failed|stats\fR]
Show history. \fB--here\fR filters to the current directory, \fB--failed\fR to non-zero exits, \fBstats\fR shows top commands and failure rates (SQLite backend only).
.TP
.B !!, !n
Repeat the last command, or the \fIn\fRth.
.SS Job control
.TP
.B bg \fIcommand\fR
Run a command in the background.
.TP
.B bglist
List background jobs.
.TP
.B bgkill \fIn\fR, bgstop \fIn\fR, bgstart \fIn\fR
Terminate, suspend, or resume background job number \fIn\fR.
.TP
.B fg \fR[\fIn\fR]
Bring a background job to the foreground.
.TP
.B trap \fR[\fI'cmd' SIG...\fR]
Install a POSIX signal/EXIT handler. \fBtrap -\fR \fISIG\fR resets, \fBtrap '' \fISIG\fR ignores. Recognizes EXIT, HUP, INT, QUIT, TERM, USR1, USR2.
.SS Files & scripts
.TP
.B source \fIfile\fR (also \fB.\fR)
Execute commands from \fIfile\fR in the current shell.
.TP
.B which \fIcmd\fR, type \fIcmd\fR
Locate a command or identify a builtin.
.SS UI & rich output
.TP
.B theme \fR[\fBlist\fR | \fBset\fR \fIname\fR | \fBpreview\fR]
Manage the color theme. Five bundled: \fBcatppuccin-mocha\fR (default), \fBcatppuccin-latte\fR, \fBtokyo-night\fR, \fBdracula\fR, \fBnord\fR.
.TP
.B explain \fIcmd\fR \fR[\fIargs...\fR]
Print inline documentation for a command and its flags (built-in database covering \fBtar\fR, \fBgrep\fR, \fBfind\fR, \fBchmod\fR, \fBls\fR, \fBgit\fR, and 25+ more).
.TP
.B copy \fR[\fItext\fR] | paste
Clipboard copy/paste via OSC 52 (works over SSH, inside tmux) with \fBpbcopy\fR/\fBxclip\fR/\fBwl-copy\fR fallbacks.
.TP
.B linkify, table, block
Rich-output helpers: wrap URLs as OSC 8 hyperlinks, render TSV/CSV as a Unicode box-drawn table, and open/close collapsible command blocks.
.TP
.B clear
Clear the screen.
.SS Sessions & config
.TP
.B session \fBsave\fR | \fBlist\fR | \fBrm\fR | \fBload\fR \fIname\fR
Persist and restore cwd, aliases, and exported environment under \fB~/.tash/sessions/\fR.
.TP
.B config \fR[\fBget\fR | \fBset\fR | \fBsync\fR \fBinit\fR|\fBremote\fR|\fBpush\fR|\fBpull\fR|\fBdiff\fR]
Manage configuration, including git-based sync across machines (keeps \fBconfig.toml\fR, themes, alias packs; excludes \fBhistory.db\fR, sessions, sockets).
.SS AI (when compiled in)
.TP
.B @ai \fR[\fIquestion | config | clear | on | off | errors on|off\fR]
Ask the AI in natural language; configure providers (Gemini, OpenAI, Ollama); clear conversation memory.
.TP
.IB "question" ?
Any line ending in \fB?\fR whose first word is not a valid command is routed to the AI, which generates a shell command you can run, edit, or cancel.
.PP
When a command fails, tash may automatically explain the error and suggest a one-keypress fix (disable with \fB@ai errors off\fR).
.SH OPERATORS
.TP
.B &&
Run next command only if the previous succeeded.
.TP
.B ||
Run next command only if the previous failed.
.TP
.B ;
Run next command unconditionally.
.TP
.B |
Pipe stdout of one command to stdin of the next.
.TP
.B |>
Structured-data pipeline (\fBwhere\fR, \fBsort-by\fR, \fBselect\fR, \fBreject\fR, \fBfirst\fR, \fBlast\fR, \fBcount\fR, \fBuniq\fR, \fBto-json\fR, \fBto-csv\fR, \fBto-table\fR).
.TP
.B ( ... )
Subshell — runs commands in a forked child so \fBcd\fR / \fBexport\fR do not leak into the parent. Works inside pipelines.
.SH REDIRECTION
.TP
.B > \fIfile\fR, >> \fIfile\fR
Redirect stdout (overwrite / append).
.TP
.B < \fIfile\fR
Redirect stdin.
.TP
.B 2> \fIfile\fR, 2>&1
Redirect stderr / merge stderr into stdout.
.TP
.B << \fIDELIM\fR, <<- \fIDELIM\fR, <<'\fIDELIM\fR', <<"\fIDELIM\fR"
Heredocs. The dash form strips leading tabs; quoted delimiter disables \fB$VAR\fR and \fB$(...)\fR expansion inside the body. Supported inside pipelines.
.SH EXPANSION
.TP
.B $VAR, ${VAR}
Environment variable expansion.
.TP
.B $?
Exit status of the previous command.
.TP
.B $$
PID of the current shell.
.TP
.B $(cmd)
Command substitution.
.TP
.B ~
Home directory expansion.
.TP
.B * ? [...]
Glob/wildcard expansion.
.SH PLUGIN TOGGLES
Any bundled provider can be disabled at startup without rebuilding by setting the matching environment variable to any non-zero value:
\fBTASH_DISABLE_FISH_COMPLETION\fR,
\fBTASH_DISABLE_FIG_COMPLETION\fR,
\fBTASH_DISABLE_MANPAGE_COMPLETION\fR,
\fBTASH_DISABLE_STARSHIP\fR,
\fBTASH_DISABLE_SQLITE_HISTORY\fR,
\fBTASH_DISABLE_SAFETY_HOOK\fR,
\fBTASH_DISABLE_ALIAS_SUGGEST\fR,
\fBTASH_DISABLE_AI_ERROR_HOOK\fR.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.tashrc
Startup commands executed when tash starts interactively.
.TP
.B ~/.tash/config.toml
Configuration file.
.TP
.B ~/.tash/history.db
SQLite-backed history (when compiled with SQLite support).
.TP
.B ~/.tash/sessions/
Persisted sessions.
.TP
.B ~/.tash/completions/fig/
Fig/Amazon Q completion specs.
.TP
.B ~/.tash/themes/
User-supplied themes (augments the bundled set).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh (1),
.BR bash (1),
.BR zsh (1),
.BR fish (1)
